description.author: David M. Johnson <djohnson.m@gmail.com>
description.description: Miso is a small isomorphic Haskell front-end framework featuring a virtual-dom, diffing / patching algorithm, event delegation, event batching, SVG, Server-sent events, Websockets, and an extensible Subscription-based subsystem. Inspired by Elm, Redux and Bobril. `IO` and other effects (like `XHR`) can be introduced into the system via the `Effect` data type. Miso makes heavy use of the GHCJS FFI and therefore has minimal dependencies.
